Chelsea are open to selling winger Hakim Ziyech this summer if they receive an important proposal for the Moroccan star. This was disclosed by football transfer expert, Fabrizio Romano, in a tweet via his Twitter handle on Tuesday. Romano also revealed that Ajax goalkeeper, André Onana, has signed a five-year deal with Inter Milan. He tweeted: “Chelsea are now open to sell Hakim Ziyech in case they receive an important proposal.” “Marcos Alonso will leave with Barça still leading the race – talks soon with N’Golo Kanté to discuss his contract situation, Jorginho waiting too.” He added in another tweet: “André Onana has just arrived at Inter headquarter. The Cameroonian GK has already signed his five year deal with Inter, announcement soon. “Onana already completed medical tests in January, it’s done – also Handanović will stay at Inter with a new deal.”